# Database migrations

## New migration files

- **Create a new migration file only when adding a new table** (including pivot tables and other new schema objects that warrant their own migration file in this project).
- **Do not** add a separate migration whose sole purpose is to change an already-migrated table (e.g. add/change/drop columns, indexes, or foreign keys on an existing table).

## Editing existing tables

- **Edit the original `create_*_table` migration** for that table when you need to change its definition.
- Keep the full column definition accurate when modifying a column (Laravel will not merge partial definitions across files if only the original exists).

## Rationale

This project prefers a single source of truth per table in its initial migration rather than follow-up alter migrations for the same table.
